column4: I opened Synaptic PAckage Manager and got this.. E: Type 'b' is not known on line 1 in source list /etc/apt/sources.list
E: The list of sources could not be read.
Go to the repository dialog to correct the problem.
Would you please put the contents of /etc/apt/sources.list in a pastebin?
I got Software Sources when I opened it.. What do I do?
Scratch that.. I found it.. Let me put it to pastebin
Those two characters at the beginning shouldn't be there
Delete the b and the space
You will need root permissions to edit the file
hit Alt + F2 and run the command 'gksudo gedit /etc/apt/sources.list'
Thanks.. I'm saving the file now
Works like a charm! Everything works.. Now how did everyone say to go about downloading the cario dock?
I open sources.list and add gksudo gedit /etc/apt/sources.list or the deb with the links? Sorry I just got Ubuntu
